      • commitAsync

        public rx.Observable<FluentModelTImpl> commitAsync()
        Commits the changes in the external child resource collection.

        This method returns an observable stream, its observer's onNext will be called for each successfully committed resource followed by 'one call to onCompleted' or one call to onError with a CompositeException containing the list of exceptions where each exception describes the reason for failure of a resource commit.

        Returns:
        the observable stream

      • commitAndGetAllAsync

        public rx.Observable<List<FluentModelTImpl>> commitAndGetAllAsync()
        Commits the changes in the external child resource collection.

        This method returns a observable stream, either its observer's onError will be called with CompositeException if some resources failed to commit or onNext will be called if all resources committed successfully.

        Returns:
        the observable stream
